member.summary:
Gives you an ID to classify a specific item module type


It may be confusing to wrap around your head what this ID is used for, but this example should help:
public static int MyCustomModuleType;
...Load()
MyCustomEquipType = ItemModuleType.GetReservedID();
...SetStaticDefaults() in a Grappling Hook Item...
ModularItemManager.Catalogue.AllowEquipType(Type, MyCustomEquipType);
